# Strict Tactile Design Adherence

## CRITICAL REQUIREMENT
**ALL components and styling MUST strictly follow the tactile design system**. No exceptions for generic Material Design, flat design, or cold aesthetics.

## Typography Enforcement

### MANDATORY Font Usage
```typescript
// ✅ REQUIRED: Proper font class usage
<h1 className="font-headline text-charcoal text-4xl font-bold">
  Headlines MUST use font-headline (Playfair Display)
</h1>

<p className="font-body text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed">
  Body text MUST use font-body (Inter)
</p>

<button className="font-body font-medium">
  UI elements MUST use font-body
</button>

// ❌ VIOLATIONS - These patterns are FORBIDDEN
<h1 className="font-sans">Wrong Font</h1>
<h1 className="font-serif">Wrong Font</h1>
<p className="font-mono">Wrong Font</p>
<button className="font-bold">Missing font-body</button>
```

### Typography Hierarchy Rules
- **Headlines (h1-h6)**: MUST use `font-headline` + `text-charcoal`
- **Body text (p, span, div)**: MUST use `font-body` + `text-charcoal/80` for secondary
- **UI elements (button, input, label)**: MUST use `font-body`
- **NEVER**: Mix serif and sans-serif inappropriately

